You have finished working on this issue. Now produce a final report as a single JSON object (no markdown fences, no commentary — ONLY the JSON).

{
  "goal": "One sentence: what the issue asked you to do",
  "attempts": [
    {
      "description": "What you tried",
      "outcome": "What happened (succeeded / failed / partial)",
      "evidence": ["Relevant output, error messages, or test results"]
    }
  ],
  "final_approach": "Which attempt solved it, or the best one if unsolved",
  "files_changed": [
    {"path": "relative/path.py", "reason": "Why this file was changed"}
  ],
  "evidence": {
    "test_output": "Copy of test/eval output that proves your changes work",
    "error_logs": "Any errors encountered (empty string if none)"
  },
  "verdict": "solved | partial | blocked",
  "confidence": 0.0,
  "blockers": ["Issues you could not resolve"],
  "next_steps": ["Suggested follow-up if not fully solved"],
  "artifacts": ["Paths to files in the workspace that support your report"]
}

Include EVERY approach you tried, even failed ones. Paste actual output as evidence, not summaries. Be honest about confidence.
